===Etymology===
{{PIE root|en|ǵneh₃}}
From {{inh|en|enm|cognicion}}, from {{der|en|la|cognitio||knowledge, perception, a judicial examination, trial}}, from {{m|la|cognitus}}, past participle of {{m|la|cognoscere||to know}}, from {{m|la|co-||together}} + {{m|la|*gnoscere}}, older form of {{m|la|noscere||to know}}; see [[know]], and compare [[cognize]], [[cognizance]], [[cognizor]], [[cognosce]], [[connoisseur]].

